    <a title="Ellen" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/907919-ellen"><img alt="Ellen" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1227982604p2/907919.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2382160261?book_show_action=true">May 04, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ellen" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ellen" href="/user/show/907919-ellen">Ellen</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/907919-ellen?shelf=non-fiction">non-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/907919-ellen?shelf=africa">africa</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/907919-ellen?shelf=development">development</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2382160261" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11375711054141719675">A shill for the development agency One Acre focusing on the everyday decision making that smallholder farmers do to balance food needs, education and healthcare, and investing for the future. As someone who worked in food aid for the briefest of times I bristled at the author&apos;s statement that no other aid agencies were focused on the distribution of seeds and fertilizers (rather than simply handing out bags of USA-grown food.) Sure, some agencies do food relief but to say that One Acre is the on</span>
  <span id="freeText11375711054141719675" style="display:none">A shill for the development agency One Acre focusing on the everyday decision making that smallholder farmers do to balance food needs, education and healthcare, and investing for the future. As someone who worked in food aid for the briefest of times I bristled at the author's statement that no other aid agencies were focused on the distribution of seeds and fertilizers (rather than simply handing out bags of USA-grown food.) Sure, some agencies do food relief but to say that One Acre is the only group out there doing what they're doing is disingenuous -- as is not discussing the larger power dynamics that cause poverty, lack of land title, and famine. One Acre does great things but needs to be set in a larger context of policy change. (Also the author was pro green revolution and eucalyptus trees, two things that destroyed Peru)</span>
  <a data-text-id="11375711054141719675" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


